{{TennisEventInfo|1996|Warsaw Cup by Heros| | date=16–22 September | edition=2nd | category=[[WTA Tier III Events|Tier III]] | draw=32S / 16D | surface=[[Clay court|Clay]] / outdoor | location=[[Warsaw]], Poland | champs={{flagicon|SVK}} [[Henrieta Nagyová]] | champd={{flagicon|UKR}} [[Olga Lugina]] / {{flagicon|BUL}} [[Elena Pampoulova]] }}
The '''1996 Warsaw Cup by Heros''' was a women's [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]] at the [[Warszawianka Tennis Centre]] in [[Warsaw]], Poland that was part of [[WTA Tier III Events|Tier III]] of the [[1996 WTA Tour]]. It was the second edition of the tournament and was held from 16 September until 22 September 1996. Unseeded [[Henrieta Nagyová]] won the singles title.
==Finals== ===Singles=== {{main|1996 Warsaw Cup by Heros – Singles}} {{flagicon|SVK}} [[Henrieta Nagyová]] defeated {{flagicon|AUT}} [[Barbara Paulus]] 3–6, 6–2, 6–1 * It was Nagyová's only title of the year and the 1st of her career.
===Doubles=== {{main|1996 Warsaw Cup by Heros - Doubles}} {{flagicon|UKR}} [[Olga Lugina]] / {{flagicon|BUL}} [[Elena Pampoulova]] defeated {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Alexandra Fusai]] / {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Laura Garrone]] 1–6, 6–4, 7–5 * It was Lugina's only title of the year and the 1st of her career. It was Pampoulova's only title of the year and the 2nd of her career.
==External links== * [http://www.itftennis.com/procircuit/tournaments/women's-tournament/info.aspx?tournamentid=1020001282 ITF tournament edition details] * [https://wtafiles.blob.core.windows.net/pdf/draws/archive/1996/680.pdf Tournament draws]
