{{Infobox football biography | name = Jamie Bosio | fullname = James Louis Bosio | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1991|9|24|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Dublin]], [[Republic of Ireland]] | height = 1.79 m | currentclub = [[Gibraltar United F.C.|Gibraltar United]] | clubnumber = 24 | position = [[Defensive midfielder]], [[defender (association football)|defender]] | youthyears1 = 1996–1999 | youthclubs1 = [[Home Farm F.C.|Home Farm]] | youthyears2 = 1999–2000 | youthclubs2 = [[Peterborough United]] | youthyears3 = 2000–2008 | youthclubs3 = [[Glacis United]] <!--all match stats are taken from the GFA website's fixtures/results page. There is no single appearances page, so refer to each individual match page--> | years1 = 2008–2013 | clubs1 = [[Glacis United]] | caps1 = 73 | goals1 = 2 | years2 = 2013–2015 | clubs2 = [[Europa F.C.|College Europa]] | caps2 = 46 | goals2 = 3 | years3 = 2015–2016 | clubs3 = [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C.|Lincoln Red Imps]] | caps3 = 1 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2015 | clubs4 = → [[Ashford United F.C.|Ashford United]] (loan) | caps4 = 4 | goals4 = 0 | years5 = 2015–2016 | clubs5 = → [[Canterbury City F.C.|Canterbury City]] (loan) | caps5 = 17 | goals5 = 2 | years6 = 2016– | clubs6 = [[Gibraltar United F.C.|Gibraltar United]] | caps6 = 55 | goals6 = 10 | nationalyears1 = 2015– | nationalteam1 = [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] | nationalcaps1= 12 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | pcupdate = 4 October 2018 | ntupdate = 25 March 2018 }}
'''James Louis 'Jamie' Bosio''' (born 24 September 1991) is a Gibraltarian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Gibraltar Premier Division]] team [[Gibraltar United F.C.|Gibraltar United]] and has twelve caps for the [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] national team. Mainly a defensive midfielder, he can also play at left back or centre back.
==Career== Bosio became Gibraltar's first captain in the [[UEFA Europa League]] when [[Europa F.C.|College Europa]] took on [[FC Vaduz]] of Liechtenstein in July 2014. He was part of the [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C.]] squad that made history by qualifying for the second round of the [[UEFA Champions League]] for the first time in July 2015.
He is currently a teacher in Gibraltar after completing his teacher training at [[Canterbury Christ Church University]] where he was awarded an Elite Sport Scholarship. He also serves as co-president and coach of [[Bavaria F.C.C.]]'s [[futsal]] team.
==International career== Bosio was eligible to represent either [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] or the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]] at international level. He decided to pledge his allegiance to Gibraltar and made his debut in their 4–0 defeat to Croatia in Varazdin on 6 June 2015 and his competitive debut against world champions Germany in the [[UEFA Euro 2016]] Qualifiers a week later.
Bosio made his first competitive start for Gibraltar against Greece in the [[FIFA World Cup 2018]] Qualifiers in September 2016.
